    {
      "id": "bb3867d7_c2f872f4",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/charts/policy-distribution/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 29,
      "message": "> Does it need to be the same as in your other review https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/105919/3/kubernetes/policy/charts/policy-api/values.yaml (the uid is different) since they point to the api component?\n\nIt's not required but let's keep it consistent\n\n@Dominic\nPlease unify naming\n\n@Jorge\nTechnically they don't need to be the same as they will go to separate secrets. As you have seen with mariadb0galera we try to do this step by step. First we move all modules to use hardcoded but placed in secret credentials and only after we have that working we use the external secret functionality to unify all related secrets in given component\n\n> Should something be done in the integration robot's healthcheck functionality to keep them in sync too?\n\nYou're perfectly right but it's the step after next step;)",
